parameters.name: R
parameters.description: Spacecraft range from the Jupiter center of mass in units of Rj where Rj = 71492 km.

parameters.name: S3_LAT
parameters.description: Spacecraft System III (1965.0) latitude in units of degrees.

parameters.name: S3_WLON
parameters.description: Spacecraft System III (1965.0) West longitude in units of degrees.

parameters.name: JSE_X
parameters.description: X component of the spacecraft range from the Jupiter center of mass in JSE coordinates. In this coordinate system, The X-Z plane contains the Jupiter-Sun vector. X lies in the equatorial plane and points sunwards. Units are Jovian radii where 1 Rj = 71492 km.

parameters.name: JSE_Y
parameters.description: Y component of the spacecraft range from the Jupiter center of mass in JSE coordinates. In this coordinate system, Y is along the dawn-dusk meridian, positive towards dusk (opposing orbital motion). Units are Jovian radii.

parameters.name: JSE_Z
parameters.description: Z component of the spacecraft range from the Jupiter center of mass in JSE coordinates. In this coordinate system, Z is parallel to Jupiter's spin axis (omega), positive northward. Units are Jovian radii.

parameters.name: JSM_X
parameters.description: X component of the spacecraft range from the Jupiter center of mass in JSM coordinates. In this coordinate system, X is along the Jupiter-Sun line, positive sunwards. Units are Jovian radii where 1 Rj = 71492 km.

parameters.name: JSM_Y
parameters.description: Y component of the spacecraft range from the Jupiter center of mass in JSM coordinates. In this coordinate system, the Y-Z plane rocks about the X-axis as the planet (and dipole) spins. Y is nominally towards dusk. Units are Jovian radii.

parameters.name: JSM_Z
parameters.description: Z component of the spacecraft range from the Jupiter center of mass in JSM coordinates. Units are Jovian radii.

parameters.name: LOCAL HOUR
parameters.description: Local hour is computed by converting the local hour angle into hours where 15 degrees equals one hour. To compute the hour angle, the S/C position is projected into the Jovian equatorial plane and then the angle is measured from the anti-sunward line (midnight) in the counter-clockwise direction.

parameters.name: MAGNETIC LOCAL HOUR
parameters.description: Magnetic local hour is similar to the local hour except that the spacecraft position is projected into the dipole equator rather than the planetographic equator.
